{"metadata":{"name":"Sunan Ibn Majah","section":{"37":{"eng-name":"Zuhd","ara-name":"كتاب الزهد"}},"section_detail":{"37":{"hadithnumber_first":4100,"hadithnumber_last":4341,"arabicnumber_first":4100,"arabicnumber_last":4341}}},"hadiths":[{"hadithnumber":4125,"arabicnumber":4125,"text":"It was narrated that Abu Hurairah said:“Ja’far bin Abu Talib used to like the poor; he would sit with them and talk to them, and they would talk to him. And the Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) gave him the Kunyah of Abul-Masakin (Father of the Poor).”","grades":[{"name":"Al-Albani","grade":"Very Daif"},{"name":"Muhammad Fouad Abd al-Baqi","grade":"Very Daif"},{"name":"Shuaib Al Arnaut","grade":"Very Daif"},{"name":"Zubair Ali Zai","grade":"Daif"}],"reference":{"book":37,"hadith":26},"chapter":{"id":7,"ara-name":"باب مُجَالَسَةِ الْفُقَرَاءِ ","eng-name":"Keeping company with the poor","isFirstHadith":true}}]}